comments: She\'s a wonderful instructor. She really cares about how well you do in class so she\'ll try to push you. One slogan she often uses is "wiggle it out" right before you give a presentation to shake off the nervousness. Shes young, pretty, helpful, and be sure to do the readings for some quizzes.

I love how she throws so much free points at the end to help you grade out :) She\'s nice, pretty, and young. Not a tough grader on presentations, tougher on the outlines though. Do take though because she\'s nicer than most of the other T.A.\'s for sure.
super chill, easy to talk to. basically what else is saying on here. grades fair, entertaining class, I felt like it was over super quick.

LOVE HER!!!! she was an awesome teacher. she was extremely funny and really wanted to get to know you individually. She wants you to do well and encourages you during your speeches. I would say take her over anyone else!
awesome, awesome, AWESOME instructor! She is extremely easy to talk to and helpful. Public speaking is horrible for most, but she makes it easier for the whole class.

Great teacher,keeps the class interested. Takes interest in her students and relateable. Loved this class even though I wasn\'t thrilled about giving speeches, she made it fun, gave tons of help and constructive criticism, gives you what you need to succeed. I went from getting C\'s ro A\'s on my last two speeches, she\'s a great teacher, take her.
She is really nice and helpful and she really likes the subject and she really wants you to improve. She grades kind of strictly but she teaches you the material so it\'s not too hard.
